        <div class="secondarymaroonicons-arssbR7" id="secondarymaroonicons">
<div class="opaqueback">
<div class="container">
<div class="section-header center text-center">
<h2>Early Graduate Admission</h2>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-4"><img alt="Welcome to TAMIU" class="img-responsive center-block" src="images/home/Welcome2tamiu.jpg" style="border-radius: 0;" width="320" /></div>
<div class="col-md-8 text-left" style="font-size: 1.1em;">
<section class="fadeInUp wow" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: .5s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
<p>TAMIU's A.R. Sanchez, Jr. School of Business is pleased to announce that international applicants applying to a business graduate program will be considered for admission review prior to the completion of their undergraduate degree.</p>
<p><strong> Applicants with six semester marks are eligible to apply and be considered for full admission while still completing their undergraduate studies. </strong></p>
<p>All international applicants fully admitted to the University and one of our three graduate programs will need to obtain an I-20 to proceed with their student visa appointment.</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Advising Center at 956-326-4622 or <a href="mailto:business@tamiu.edu">business@tamiu.edu</a></p>
</section>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
